write_up: Everyone’s heard a Radiohead song. Some part of their aura will always seem above all other earthly indie bands, but the 2010s saw the first decade of indie music where Radiohead was not a major player. ‘Identikit’, and ‘A Moon Shaped Pool’ in general, suggest though that the core songwriters could continue to make great music for the foreseeable future (The Smile). ‘Identikit’s guitars meander through shifting backgrounds of soft choruses that rise and fall to produce a surprisingly ear-wormy final product.
